    {
      "id": "p002",
      "index": 2,
      "source": "The catch-up cost to replicate TSMC’s capability would require an annual capex of $50B+ (vs TSMC’s $30-35B) just to play catch-up. The density of human capital creates an insurmountable barrier. TSMC deploys 70,000+ process engineers, whereas Apple would need to build this workforce from scratch.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0356",
      "parent_block_index": 356,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "The catch-up cost to replicate TSMC’s capability would require an annual capex of $50B+ (vs TSMC’s $30-35B) just to play catch-up. The density of human capital creates an insurmountable barrier. TSMC deploys 70,000+ process engineers, whereas Apple would need to build this workforce from scratch.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "The catch-up cost to replicate TSMC’s capability would require an annual capex of $50B+ (vs TSMC’s $30-35B) just to play catch-up. The density of human capital creates an insurmountable barrier. TSMC deploys 70,000+ process engineers, whereas Apple would need to build this workforce from scratch.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
