    {
      "id": "p003",
      "index": 3,
      "source": "For Apple, the return on invested capital (ROIC) of building a fab is negative. Using TSMC’s balance sheet as a service allows Apple to maintain 35-40% corporate operating margins. Owning a fab would dilute those margins significantly while introducing operational risks (yield crashes, node delays) that Apple currently outsources.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0357",
      "parent_block_index": 357,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "For Apple, the return on invested capital (ROIC) of building a fab is negative. Using TSMC’s balance sheet as a service allows Apple to maintain 35-40% corporate operating margins. Owning a fab would dilute those margins significantly while introducing operational risks (yield crashes, node delays) that Apple currently outsources.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "For Apple, the return on invested capital (ROIC) of building a fab is negative. Using TSMC’s balance sheet as a service allows Apple to maintain 35-40% corporate operating margins. Owning a fab would dilute those margins significantly while introducing operational risks (yield crashes, node delays) that Apple currently outsources.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
      "segment_start": 0,
      "segment_end": 332,
      "expected_tokens": [],
      "format_recovery_status": "not_applicable",
      "format_errors": [],
      "is_heading": false,
      "heading_level": null,
      "heading_chain": [],
      "is_metadata": false,
      "metadata_type": null,
      "translations": {
        "pro": {
          "text": "对苹果而言，自建晶圆厂的投资资本回报率（ROIC）为负。将台积电的资产负债表作为一种服务（BaaS）来使用，让苹果得以维持35%至40%的公司营业利润率。自持晶圆厂将大幅稀释这一利润率，并引入良率崩溃、节点延迟等运营风险，而苹果目前已将这些风险转嫁给代工厂。",
          "model": "pro",
          "created_at": "2026-04-10T22:01:36.077062",
          "tokenized_text": null,
          "format_issues": []
        }
      },
